\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0
\cf2 Recommendation 4: Establish a Dynamic User Skill Profile: Synthesize the data gathered from the Can-Do self-assessment and the diagnostic tasks to create an initial, detailed user skill profile. This profile should move beyond a single proficiency label to represent the user's abilities across a range of fine-grained linguistic skills. These could include specific grammar points (e.g., classifier usage, past tense markers), vocabulary domains (e.g., food, travel, business), pronunciation features (e.g., mastery of specific tones, consonant clusters), and functional competencies (e.g., ability to make requests, describe events). This profile could potentially be represented internally as a skill vector, vskill , where each dimension corresponds to a specific skill.[18, 19, 20] Crucially, this profile must be 
