\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0 \cf2 Critique of Current Form: The existing linear form structure for the Set Wizard, while straightforward, is likely inadequate for effectively capturing the more nuanced inputs required by the proposed enhancements to proficiency assessment (Section II.A) and structured goal setting (Section II.B) [User Query]. Standard forms can feel rigid, lack interactive guidance, and may not easily accommodate the exploratory or iterative nature of defining personalized learning needs.[23, 61]\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0
\cf2 Exploring Alternatives:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa160\partightenfactor0
\ls23\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Conversational UI (Chatbot): Implementing the wizard as a purely conversational interface, where users interact with a chatbot using natural language, offers potential benefits in terms of personalization, engagement, and guidance.[62, 63, 64] A chatbot can explain steps, ask clarifying questions, and adapt the flow based on user responses, feeling more like a helpful tutor than a static form. However, pure CUI can suffer from ambiguity in interpreting user input, potential inefficiency for structured data entry (like selecting from many options), and may frustrate users if the natural language understanding is imperfect.[65]\
\ls23\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Traditional Forms (Enhanced): The existing form could be significantly improved with better visual structure (e.g., using cards for scenarios), clearer instructions, help text/tooltips, and progressive disclosure (revealing sections step-by-step). However, even an enhanced form might struggle to provide the dynamic guidance and flexibility needed for co-creating personalized learning goals and content.[61]\
\ls23\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Hybrid UI: This approach seeks to combine the strengths of both conversational and graphical interfaces.[61, 64, 66] It might involve using a conversational agent (potentially the chatbot proposed in Section V) to provide overall guidance, explanations, and handle freeform refinements, while employing interactive graphical elements for specific, structured tasks. Examples include tapping visual cards to select scenarios, interacting with a checklist of Can-Do statements, or using standard sliders for tone control.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0
\cf2 Recommendation 25: Adopt a Hybrid UI for the Set Wizard: It is recommended that Donkey Bridge transitions the Set Wizard to a hybrid UI model. This model would feature a guiding conversational agent (perhaps embodied by the Donkey mascot) that assists the user throughout the set creation process. This agent can introduce steps, offer explanations (e.g., "Let's figure out your current Thai level based on what you can do"), ask clarifying questions, and facilitate the review/refinement of generated content. Alongside this conversational guidance, the interface should utilize optimized graphical elements for specific inputs:\
* Interactive Can-Do statements for self-assessment (e.g., checkable list items or cards).\
* Visually appealing cards for selecting learning scenarios.\
* Standard, well-labeled sliders for tone adjustment.\
* Clear text fields for optional topic refinement.\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa160\partightenfactor0
\ls24\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Rationale: A hybrid UI offers the best of both worlds. It provides the natural, supportive guidance of a conversational interface [63], reducing user uncertainty and making the process feel more interactive. Simultaneously, it leverages the efficiency, clarity, and reduced ambiguity of graphical controls for tasks involving selection from predefined options or structured input.[61, 64] This approach balances flexibility and support with structure and user control, making it well-suited for the complex task of personalized learning setup.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0
\cf2 The choice of interface is not merely aesthetic; it directly influences the quality of the data collected for personalization and the user's willingness to engage with the process. A pure form might be efficient for users who know exactly what they want but offers little support for exploration or clarification, potentially leading to suboptimal inputs.[61] A purely conversational interface, while potentially more engaging initially, risks ambiguity and inefficiency, especially when dealing with structured concepts like proficiency levels or predefined scenarios.[63, 65] The hybrid model [64, 66] provides a framework where the conversational agent can guide the user effectively, while well-designed graphical elements ensure that critical inputs (like proficiency assessment via Can-Do statements or goal selection via scenarios) are captured accurately and efficiently.\
This careful balance between guidance, efficiency, and user control is paramount. The interface must empower users to express their needs clearly while providing the necessary structure and support to translate those needs into effective personalization parameters. An intuitive and engaging hybrid UI is therefore critical not just for usability but for the fundamental success of the app's enhanced didactic approach, as the quality of personalization hinges directly on the quality of the input data collected through this interface.[18, 22, 23]\
