Furthermore, the design of the onboarding process can significantly impact user motivation and perception of necessary setup tasks. Tasks like proficiency assessment, while pedagogically crucial, can feel like a chore.[68] Adopting techniques from successful apps like Duolingo, which uses interactive quizzes, progress bars, and a generally gamified feel during onboarding [67, 69, 70], can transform these setup steps. By making assessment and goal-setting feel like the first part of the learning game itself, rather than a barrier to entry, the app can increase completion rates for these vital steps and foster a more positive initial engagement.[71]\
