\fs32 \cf2 A. Defining the Chatbot's Role and Personality: An Educational Guide\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0 \cf2 Rationale for Chatbot: Integrating a conversational agent, or chatbot, into the Set Wizard offers a powerful way to enhance the personalization process. A chatbot can provide real-time guidance, clarify user needs, facilitate exploration of options, and enable users to actively co-create their learning content, making the wizard more interactive, supportive, and ultimately more effective.[2, 23, 38, 58]\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0
\cf2 Recommendation 36: Define the Chatbot's Role: The chatbot's primary function within the Set Wizard should be that of a Pedagogical Guide and Co-creator.[38, 58, 79] Its key responsibilities include:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa160\partightenfactor0
\ls32\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Guiding: Assisting users through the steps of proficiency assessment (Can-Do statements, diagnostics) and goal selection (scenarios, topics).\
\ls32\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Clarifying: Helping users articulate their learning needs more precisely (e.g., "You mentioned 'business Thai' \'96 are you interested in meetings, emails, or casual conversation?").\
\ls32\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Facilitating Refinement: Presenting the LLM-generated flashcard set for review and enabling users to iteratively request changes ("Can you make this phrase sound more natural?", "Suggest a funnier mnemonic for this one.", "Replace this card, it's not relevant.").\
\ls32\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Supporting: Answering user questions related to the set creation process, Thai language basics relevant to the generated content, or how to use app features like the tone slider.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0
\cf2 Recommendation 37: Design an Engaging Personality: The chatbot's personality should align with the overall Donkey Bridge brand \'96 helpful, encouraging, knowledgeable, and incorporating the app's characteristic playfulness, but always prioritizing effective learning.[80, 81, 82, 83]\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa160\partightenfactor0
\ls33\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Core Traits: Patient, supportive, clear communicator, knowledgeable (about Thai basics and the app), encouraging, slightly witty/playful (especially if the user selects a higher "ridiculousness" setting), but never overly distracting or silly.[81, 82] Its primary goal is to facilitate learning.\
\ls33\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Visual Representation: The Donkey mascot could serve as the chatbot's avatar, reinforcing brand identity.[80, 84]\
\ls33\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Tone & Style: Conversational, friendly, approachable.[82] Use of emojis could be appropriate but should be measured. The tone could potentially adapt slightly based on the user's seriousness slider setting \'96 offering more jokes or playful language at higher settings, and being more direct and focused at lower settings.\
\ls33\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
